# Twig UI (Fantager)

Authoritative doc: `docs/ui-guidelines.md`. Quick ref: `docs/ui-agent-cheatsheet.md`.

## Never add to Twig `class` (use SCSS semantic classes)

Layout/spacing utilities: `flex`, `grid grid-cols-*`, `gap-*`, `space-y-*`, `space-x-*`, `justify-*`, `items-*`, `m*-*`, `p*-*`, `col-span-*`, `lg:*`, `md:*`, `sm:*`

Typography utilities: `text-xs|sm|lg|xl|2xl|…`, `font-semibold|bold|medium`, `text-center`

Color utilities: `text-red-*`, `bg-emerald-*`, `text-warning`, any Tailwind palette class

Sizing/FX: `w-*`, `h-*`, `min-h-[…]`, `max-h-[…]`, `shadow-lg`, `overflow-x-auto`, `whitespace-nowrap`, `cursor-pointer`

Inline `style="…"` (except truly dynamic values handled server-side).

## Allowed exceptions in Twig

- `hidden` — Stimulus toggles
- `sr-only` — screen reader text
- `group` — hover group states (rare)

## Before inventing a new class

1. Search `assets/styles/components/` for an existing class
2. If missing: add to the correct `_*.scss` using `var(--…)` tokens
3. Then use the semantic class in Twig

## Layout — prefer these (see `_layout.scss`, `_shared.scss`)

| Need | Class |
|------|-------|
| Vertical stack | `.layout-stack` (+ `--sm`, `--md`, `--lg`, `--form`) |
| Horizontal row | `.layout-cluster` (+ modifiers) |
| Page width | `.page-shell` |
| 3-column screen | `.screen-3col`, `__main`, `__aside` |
| 2-column screen | `.screen-grid`, `__main`, `__aside` |
| 2-col dashboard | `.dashboard-grid-2` |
| Form field stack | `.form-field-group` (+ `--tight`) |
| Scrollable table | `.data-table-wrap`, `.game-panel--scroll` |
| Panel | `.game-panel`, `.hero-panel`, `.feature-panel` |

## Atoms (two-class pattern where applicable)

```twig
<button class="btn btn-primary btn--sm">…</button>
<input class="form-input" id="…">
<label class="form-label" for="…">…</label>
<a class="link">…</a>
```

## Copy & status colors

Use `.copy-muted`, `.copy-secondary`, `.copy-status-error`, `.status-chip`, `.alert-box--spaced` — not Tailwind color utilities.

## i18n & a11y (required)

- All visible text: `{{ 'key'|trans }}`
- Every input: `<label for="id">` or `aria-label`
- Icon-only buttons: `aria-label="{{ '…'|trans }}"`
- Modals: `role="dialog"`, `aria-modal="true"`, `aria-labelledby`
- Dynamic alerts: `role="alert"`

## Dynamic UI

Clone from `<template id="template-…">` in Twig — do not build HTML strings with class names in JS.

## Optional verification (user-requested only)

Do not run automatically. When the user asks:

```bash
bash scripts/check-ui-compliance.sh
```
